Pluto is a famous dwarf planet in the Kuiper Belt, discovered in 1930, known for its icy, rocky surface, thin atmosphere (nitrogen, methane), five moons (largest is Charon), and frigid temperatures, but reclassified in 2006 by the IAU because it doesn't clear its orbit, unlike the eight major planets. NASA's New Horizons mission provided stunning close-up views in 2015, revealing mountains, glaciers, and a complex geological world, challenging previous views of it as a simple, dead world
